            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1215.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>shredded cabbage</strong> and <strong>grated carrot</strong> to the <strong>pickling liquor</strong> and set aside until serving &ndash; this is your&nbsp;<strong>speedy sauerkraut</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1215.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1215.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1215.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1215.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1215.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>curry powder</strong> and cook for 30 sec or until fragrant</p>\r\n<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>tomato frito</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until thickened to the consistency of ketchup &ndash; this is your <strong>curry ketchup&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1215.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1215.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1215.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1215.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1215.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice the <strong>brown&nbsp;onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Once the <strong>curry ketchup</strong> is done, transfer it to a bowl and wipe the pan clean</p>\r\n<p>Return the pan to a medium-low heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 10-12 min or until soft and caramelised&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1215.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
